    <br><br>
    <b>Description</b><br>
Talk with Sulgar the wizard who can be found along the North wall in Everfrost.  He will tell you that he is looking for tartons wheel.  If you decide to help him locate this whell he will give you a Glowing Case and a Tome of Hints.  the case is used to hold all the spokes of the wheel, the different pieces of rods and the tome tells you where to locate the rod pieces.  The Glowing Case will disapear when you log, so do not put anything in it, until you have all ten rods.  Once you have them all, put them in the case and hit combine.  This will create the Staff of the Wheel and the Star of Eyes, both needed to complete the quest for the Ice Comet spell.  The ten different rod pieces you need to locate are as follows.
<ul>
<li> [Azia] Found on the ocean floor in Eruds Crossing [-1162, 2340]
<li> [Beza] Found in the underwater cave in Everfrost.  It is in the "house" all the way back and right in the cave, where three dry bones guard spawn
<li> [Caza] Underneath the first island in Lake RatheTear you see a tunnel leading to a stone tower.  Its on the top floor of the tower.
<li> [Dena] Right outside the entrance to Kedge Keep in Dagnor's Cauldrun is where this rod spawns, if you face with your back to Kedge, it is directly diagagonal left.
<li> [Ena] Found in Lower Guk, head to the Reanimated hand room as it spawns right on the floor. 
<li> [Fana] In the Oasis of Marr, the rod is in the underwater tower near the Spectres.
<li> [Geza] In Highhold Pass, near the waterfall closest to the Tiger Inn is where the rod spawns.  
<li> [Heda] Found in the shark pit, within the Qeynos Aqueducts
<li> [Izah] Found in front of the bar called "The Blind Fish", in Neriak.  It spawns in the water.
<li> [Jaka] Found underwater in the Estate of Unrest.  To the right of the house there is a gazeebo, behind it there is a small pond, jump in and follow the tunnel to the right.<br><br>
<b>Player Comments</b> (total:6, showing:1-5) <a href="JavaScript:popComment('comment.php3?type=item&tid=81')">add</a><br>
<a href="mailto:roaryw@hotmail.com">Nupe Diggs</a> of the Tribunal server on Apr. 27, 2000 at 09:47am said...<br>
BEWARE OF THE KILLER SHARKS IN ERUDS CROSSING

I have a level 36 (now 35) wizard and I was killed in an instant like nothing by a group of killer sharks which sit over the rod at eruds crossing.  It took me 2 days to get my corpse back and many high level bards (who couldnt swim away fast enough) we killed trying to help me -- all above level 40.

If there is a trick to getting this -- please let me know --- but im not going down there again until at least level 55 when i have some absurd damage ability<br><br>
<a href="mailto:none@I.Have.none">Daemonn</a> of the Tribunal server on Apr. 03, 2000 at 10:33am said...<br>
I got my staff last night at level 25. It took a good long day to get 9 of the 10 pieces (all but lower Guk) with the description here to lead my way. Invisibility is your friend on this quest. You will need shallow breath for a couple of the parts. I had a magician friend that would summon a shallow breath stone, then send me on my way until I needed another. As for Lower Guk - I want during out server's most busy time and it was a BITCH. I could not have done it alone - ever. Some kind soul cast invisibility to undead and another very kind high level wizard came and escorted me to the room (after her party cleaned out the room).<br><br>
<a href="mailto:djinn24@msn.com">Famwenie Silvermist</a> of the E'Ci server on Jan. 20, 2000 at 02:31pm said...<br>
I wouldn't suggest trying this quest unit you are lvl 25+.  Six or seven of the rods are really easy to get and the remaining are not incredibly hard to get.  A few helpful hints for a couple of the rods.  Use invisable for the rods in the underwater tower and at the killer sharks.  When I did the quest the creatures conned indifferent while I was invisable.  When going to get the LGuk rod go when your server has 1600-2000 people on.  That way you can just about ensure L Guk will be completly camped and a lvl 1 could walk down and get the Rod 8?).  If you have any questions and our an E'Ci give me a tell.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:fonzie@ibm.net">Ignia</a> of the Rodsent Nife server on Dec. 13, 1999 at 04:46pm said...<br>
*Continued again*

9. Izah- Neriak is correct, but its in the water in front of the bar called "the blind fish", 
the bar has 4 glass windows that are underwater, and the rod spawns right infront of those windows.
10.Jaka- Its in unrest but not near a mob that drops dwarven armor, its in the water outside the
right side of the house near wherer the the gnome spelunker is, instead of goin into the tunnel that leads to him, you go a little right of that entracnce and theres a very short passage, there lies the rod.

---- Cut ---

Good luck

Ignia
